title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return user recognizable strings
description: When using the get column label function from the meta data object, the labels returned before extraction are null. However, after extraction, the labels should be recognizable strings to the user.
OB: The labels returned before extraction are null.
EB: The labels after extraction should be recognizable strings to the user.
SR:
1. Obtain the meta data object.
2. Use the get column label function from the meta data object.
3. Verify that the labels returned are null.
4. Extract the labels from the meta data object.
5. Verify that the extracted labels are recognizable strings to the user.
